# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Planned]
### Added
|Feature|Example Features|Benefit
|:-|:-|:-|
|Regrouping|Nested, virtual, tag-based|Dynamic, rule-based file views

## [Unreleased]

### Added

- This CHANGELOG file to hopefully keep a track of all features that will be added.
- README to explain the project and how to use it.
- MIT license because we <3 open-source projects.
- List all files extensions in a folder and subfolders
- Classify document using dynamic filters and dynamic strategy so you can add your own pluggins
    - Multi-source directory
    - The basics filters added are :
        - filter files based on their extensions
        - filter files based on a regex pattern
    - The basics strategies added are :
        - classify files based on their last modified date
        - classify files based on the src hierachy folder
    - An option for parallelism to speedup the process
    - Stats on files a processing them
    - Conflict are handle in 3 different ways (skip, overwrite or rename)
        - default comportement of rename is ti check if the file is the same before moving it, if it is, it will skip it
    - Dry-run is also possible showing you the stats



